The Iraqi government spent £56million
on the fake bomb detectors, some of which was paid as bribes to senior 
figures. These included General Jihad al-Jabiri, head of the Baghdad 
bomb squad, who helped McCormick win the massive contract. He and two 
other Iraqi officials are now serving jail terms for corruption.

